The paper proposes two algorithms for solving large-scale RMDPs using deep neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithms also incorporate robustness considerations, which are relevant to control systems and robotics research (cs.SY, cs.RO). Additionally, the paper mentions Bayesian methods, which are commonly used in neural network research (cs.NE).
